GOAL: Add audio phrases to the app
STEPS:
1. Create new constructor and hide unused views
2. Add ArrayList and set Adapter
3. Set OnItemClickListener
4. Create: MediaPlayer, AudioManager, AudioManager.onAudioFocusChangeListener, OnCompletion Callback
5. Code onAudioFocusChangeListener to handle requests from the OS.
6. Add onStop override method
7. Create releaseMediaPlayer method, add to onCompletion
8. Instantiate mAudioManager in onCreateView: 
	mAudioManager = (AudioManager) getActivity().getSupportService(Context.AUDIO_SERVICE)
9. When item clicked, request AudioFocus from mAudioManager. 
	- requestAudioFocus arguments: changeListener, Type, Duration
	- Returns a CONSTANT with integer value
	int requestFocus = mAudioManager.requestAudioFocus(changeListener, AudioManager.STREAM_MUSIC, AudioManager.AUDIOFOCUS_GAIN_TRANSIENT) 

10. Create If-then statement to handle requestAudioFocus return value
	if (requestFocus == AudioManager.AUDIOFOCUS_REQUEST_GRANTED){
		mMediaPlayer = MediaPlayer.create(getActivity(), item.getAudio());
		mMediaPlayer.start()
		mMediaPlayer.setOnCompletionListener(mCompletionListener)
		
